T.C : O(1)
S.C : O(1)

Set rightmost unset bit: turn the rightmost 0 into 1
Unset rightmost unset bit: turn the rightmost 0 into 0 explicitly (clear it if itâ€™s 1):

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n = 18;

        // Set rightmost unset bit
        int setResult = n | (n + 1);

        // Unset rightmost unset bit
        int unsetResult = n & (n + 1);

        System.out.println(n);
        System.out.println("After setting rightmost unset bit: " + setResult);
        System.out.println("After unsetting rightmost unset bit: " + unsetResult);
    }
}
